# GSL component authoring

## Module layout

```
src/components/{name}/
  {Name}.tsx
  index.ts
  styles/{name}.css    # BEM: gsl-{name}__*
  {Name}.test.tsx
src/types/{name}.ts    # props, classNames, unions
```

## Styling

- Use `--gsl-*` tokens from `src/styles/theme/`; no hardcoded theme colors, sizes, or shadows.
- Prefix classes `gsl-{component}` / `gsl-{component}__part`.
- Import CSS in the component file.
- Component-scoped tokens: `--gsl-{component}-{name}`, named so `generate-theme-tokens.mjs`'s `classify()` infers the right type (e.g. include `size`/`radius`/`shadow`/`font`/`color` in the name). See the full token & theme checklist in `AGENTS.md`.

## Responsive

Every public component must work from **320px** through desktop widths.

| Requirement | Guidance |
|-------------|----------|
| **Breakpoint** | Default mobile breakpoint: `@media (max-width: 768px)`. Document a different value in the component docs **Notes** when needed. |
| **Layout** | No horizontal overflow at 320px; use `min-width: 0`, `max-width: 100%`, `flex-wrap`, or stacked layouts on small screens. |
| **Touch targets** | Interactive controls at least **40×40px** hit area on mobile (padding or min-height), matching Button `md`. |
| **Portals / overlays** | Popovers, dropdowns, modals, and mobile drawers must fit the viewport (max width/height, scrollable content, dismiss on overlay). |
| **Motion** | Respect `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` — disable or shorten animations and transitions. |
| **Docs preview** | Interactive previews must remain usable in a narrow canvas; layout components need explicit mobile behavior. |

Before marking component work done:

- Spot-check at **320px** and **768px** — no clipped controls or sideways scroll on the component root.
- Confirm mobile behavior is implemented in CSS or JS, not desktop-only styles.
- Document non-obvious responsive behavior in the docs **Notes** section.

## Props and classNames

- Types in `src/types/{name}.ts`; re-export from component `index.ts` and `src/index.ts`.
- Provide **`classNames`** for stylable sub-parts; merge with `cn()` from `src/utils/cn.ts`:

```ts
export interface ExampleClassNames {
  root?: string;
}

export interface ExampleProps {
  classNames?: ExampleClassNames;
  className?: string; // merges with classNames.root on native elements
}
```

```tsx
className={cn("gsl-example", classNames?.root, className)}
```

- Never remove base `gsl-*` classes; append consumer classes (Tailwind-friendly).

## Tests

- Vitest + Testing Library; cover disabled, loading, and key interactions.

## Required on every public API change

Do not finish component work without all four:

1. **CHANGELOG.md** — entry under `[Unreleased]` (`Added` / `Changed` / `Fixed`).
2. **README.md** — usage summary and link to docs page (insert the `##` section in alphabetical order among other components).
3. **Docs site** — add or update `demo/docs/pages/{slug}.mdx`:
   - Examples (`ExampleTabs` when useful)
   - **Props** table
   - **Types** section for every exported type/interface/union
   - Nav entry in `demo/docs/nav.ts` (insert in alphabetical order by `slug` in the Components section)
4. **Tokens & theme** — if any `--gsl-*` token was added or renamed: run `npm run generate:tokens`; if it's a global token (not component-scoped), add a mapping in the `@theme` block at `src/styles/theme/tokens.css`; verify light + dark values exist; refresh the MCP index (`npm run build:mcp`) and confirm via `get_tokens`/`get_component`. Full checklist in `AGENTS.md`.

### Doc examples (single source)

Interactive examples must not duplicate JSX between the preview and Code tab:

1. Add or update `demo/docs/previews/examples/{name}.example.tsx` with the full runnable example (export a named component).
2. Wire `demo/docs/previews/code/*Preview.tsx` to render that example (canvas wrappers only).
3. In the MDX page, import the same file with `?raw` and pass it to `ExampleTabs` via the `code` prop:

```mdx
import exampleSource from "../previews/examples/button-variants.example.tsx?raw";

<ExampleTabs title="Variants" preview={<ButtonPreview />} code={exampleSource} />
```

Do not author separate fenced code blocks for `ExampleTabs` children.

## Exports

- Add `export * from "./components/{name}"` to `src/index.ts`.
- Keep `theme` first; list all other component exports **alphabetically by folder name** (e.g. `app-switcher`, `button`, `checkbox`).

## Component lists (alphabetical)

When adding or editing component inventories, keep **A–Z order** by component folder slug (`src/components/{name}/`):

| Location | Sort by |
|----------|---------|
| [`demo/docs/nav.ts`](demo/docs/nav.ts) — `Components` items | `slug` |
| [`src/index.ts`](src/index.ts) — component exports | folder name (`theme` stays first) |
| [`README.md`](README.md) — component `##` sections | section title (e.g. AppSwitcher, Button, …) |

Insert new components at the correct alphabetical position; do not append to the end unless it is last alphabetically.
